{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e97679e0-6006-4190-b417-789b639977af","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. For **analyzing** an existing `.dmp` file, here are the recommended approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-file.dmp>\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using `lldb` (Linux/macOS):**\n```bash\ndotnet symbol --modules <path-to-file.dmp>   # download symbols\nlldb --core <path-to-file.dmp>\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg (Windows):**\nOpen the dump, load SOS (`.loadby sos clr`), then use `!clrstack`, `!pe`, `!threads`.\n\nWould you like help installing any of these tools or running specific commands against your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6b8c03fa-70c4-453a-a68b-ed7731b4ce49","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze an existing dump, not collect one.\n\nLet me provide guidance on analyzing the dump file directly.","outputTokens":402},"id":"b81e3e46-63e8-467f-9364-00f83a5082b4","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:02:16.005Z","parentId":"f13bd858-ce3d-447f-9f1f-c6891abc819e"}
